The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Thursday, December 25, 2003 				 Assam Company rights issue cleared
 OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT																								Calcutta, Dec. 24: The board of Assam Company today approved a rights issue whereby the shareholders will get one share of Rs 10 against five held by them at a premium. The company is silent on the amount of premium the shareholders have to pay but market sources say it plans to charge a premium of Rs 10.																								The total paid-up equity of the company is Rs 22 crore and the number of shares is 2.23 crore. Following this rights issue, 44.79 lakh shares will be issued to the existing shareholders of the company. The promoters of the company hold nearly 80 per cent in the company.																								The funds from the rights issue will be used for our expansion. Moreover, the amount is interest free, senior officials said. 																								The company will be able to mop up Rs 9 crore through this rights issue. 
